Let us then ſacrifice Praiſe to the GOD of Armies, who has led our victorious Troops into this ſtrong City, of which our Enemies were ready to boaſt, as if it was invincible, The Royal Pſalmiſt inquired, Who will bring me into the ſtrong City: who will lead me into Edom? Wilt not Thou, O God?
                  Pſalm 108.10, 11. Yes, ſurely. This is the Lord's Doing, it is marvellous in our Eves. Who is like unto Thee, O Lord, fearful in Praiſes, doing Wonders. Thy right Hand, O Lord, is become Glorious in Power;


                  Thy right Hand, O Lord, bath daſhed in Pieces the Enemy.
